The paper deals with data structures and algorithms for efficient compression and manipulation of strings represented as context-free grammars. This falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses applications in information retrieval (cs.IR), deep learning (cs.DL), and machine learning (cs.LG).
